.heading .bd 3. Obtaining a copy of MAILER                              00312970
.sr c03 = &sysppage                                                     00313960
.in +.33i                                                               00314950
.sp 2                                                                   00315940
.us \The code for \MAILER\ is available in two different forms,         00316930
an object distribution and a source distribution.                       00317920
The source distribution is a superset of the object distribution (i.e.  00318910
it is not necessary to retrieve the object distribution if you request  00319900
a source distribution).                                                 00320890
.sp                                                                     00321880
The object distribution provides everything necessary to run            00322870
.us MAILER.                                                             00323860
This includes programs, text libraries, execs, and data files used in   00324850
.us \generating the routing table for \MAILER\.                         00325840
It also includes some tools that allow you to create exits that         00326830
.us \\MAILER\ can use for routing mail without having to modify         00327820
.us \\MAILER\ itself.                                                   00328810
.sp                                                                     00329800
The source distribution includes everything in the object distribution  00330790
and additionally provides all the base source files and updates to them.00331780
The updates provide either fixes for problems or additional function    00332770
.us \for the \MAILER\ code.                                             00333760
.sp                                                                     00334750
The source distribution is designed to allow a site to modify the       00335740
.us \functioning of \MAILER\ in more drastic ways than can be done in   00336730
routing exits.                                                          00337720
All files are maintained using XEDIT with the CTL option and the        00338710
CMS VMFASM and EXECUPDT commands.                                       00339700
.sp                                                                     00340690
.us \The \MAILER\ distribution files are kept on the LISTSERV at node   00341680
PUCC.                                                                   00342670
.us \Instructions for retrieving a copy of \MAILER\ from the LISTSERV   00343660
can be found in Section 6, "Installation Procedure".                    00344650
.sp 1                                                                   00345640
.us \If you will be maintaining \MAILER\ for multiple nodes you will    00346630
need to request the appropriate distribution only once.                 00347620
You do not need to make a request for each machine on which             00348610
.us \\MAILER\ will be run.                                              00349600
