.heading .bd 6. Installation Procedure                                  00506570
.sr c06 = &sysppage                                                     00506760
.in +.33i                                                               00506950
.sp 2                                                                   00507140
The following instructions assume the use of a particular disk layout.  00507330
It is not necessary to use the layout described here, but you have to   00507520
work out your own installation and maintenance procedures if you don't. 00507710
.sp                                                                     00507900
The standard installation process uses two (2) userids.                 00508090
One userid is used to maintain the mailer code.                         00508280
.us \The second userid is where \MAILER\ is run.                        00508470
The userid used for the mail maintenance id is usually MAILMNT.         00508660
The mail server's id is usually MAILER.                                 00508850
It is not necessary for you to follow this convention, but these are    00509040
the ids that will be used in the following instructions.                00509230
A skeleton directory entry for the standard maintenance userid is       00509420
defined in Appendix E.                                                  00509610
A skeleton directory entry for the standard                             00509800
.us \\MAILER\ userid is defined in Appendix F.                          00509990
.sp                                                                     00510180
To make these instructions less confusing, the mail server will be      00510370
referred to as the mailer DVM (disconnected virtual machine).           00510560
.us \Wherever you see \MAILER\ it will refer to the mailer program.     00510750
.sp 2                                                                   00510940
.subhead 6.1. Create the mail server DVM and mail maintenance ids.      00511130
.sr c0601 = &sysppage                                                   00511320
.footnote                                                               00511510
Please don't change the mailer DVM's userid without first updating your 00511700
node data base entry and waiting for it to be redistributed to all      00511890
./ R 00516000 00554000 $ 516080 80                    09/18/89 17:39:12
You may end up having to run two copies of                              00516080
.us \\MAILER\                                                           00516160
during the transition period; one under the old userid and              00516240
one under the new userid, to avoid any disruption in mail traffic.      00516320
.footend                                                                00516400
.in +.33i                                                               00516480
.sp                                                                     00516560
The mailer DVM should have a minimum virtual storage size of 1M.        00516640
Because tables and headers are stored in memory during mail processing  00516720
it is best to define the default storage size as 2M or more.            00516800
.sp                                                                     00516880
The mailer DVM's 191 is used to store incoming mail.                    00516960
It must be of adequate size to hold the largest mail file you anticipate00517040
receiving.                                                              00517120
.us \It is preferable to overallocate, because \MAILER\ does not        00517200
recover gracefully from full disk conditions (maybe in a future release 00517280
it will do better).                                                     00517360
.sp                                                                     00517440
.us \\MAILER\ normally sends msgs to local users announcing delivery    00517520
of mail.                                                                00517600
These messages will be sent using the CP MSG command unless the         00517680
mailer DVM is allowed to use the CP MSGNOH command.                     00517760
To us MSGNOH, the mailer DVM must be defined with privilege class B.    00517840
.in -.33i                                                               00517920
.sp 2                                                                   00518000
