;**                                                                     02173000
msgcmd=MSG                   ; Send messages using MSG                  02174000
;**                                                                     02175000
;** You may specify a prefix to be used on msgs issued by the LOCAL     02176000
;** or PROFS exits.  These messages announce the arrival of new mail    02177000
;** for the user.  If you do not specify a prefix, a prefix of '*'      02178000
;** will be used.  You will need to remove the ';' at the start of      02179000
;** line to use the msgprefix value.                                    02180000
;**                                                                     02181000
;** *Note* It is recommended that the msgprefix value begin with an     02182000
;** asterisk ('*') so that msgs to servers (such as listserv) will      02183000
;** not be handled as commands.                                         02184000
;**                                                                     02185000
; msgprefix=                 ; Prefix for local delivery messages       02186000
;**                                                                     02187000
;** Leave the following value FALSE if you do not want to log (display  02188000
